Reasoning: The paper deals with the Short Secluded Path problem, which is a graph problem. The focus of the paper is on parameterized complexity and data reduction, which suggests that it belongs to the categories of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The problem also involves graph theory concepts such as treewidth, feedback vertex number, and feedback edge number, which are covered in the categories of computational geometry (cs.CG), graph theory (cs.GT), and computational complexity (cs.CC).
